# Integration/E2E Tests Directory

This directory contains integration and end-to-end tests that run outside the service container.

Integration tests should:
- Test interactions between components
- Use real external services (MongoDB, Kafka)
- Verify API contracts
- Test complete user flows

## Running Integration Tests

```bash
# Start services first
docker-compose up -d

# Run integration tests from host
npm run test:integration

# Or run inside a separate test container
docker-compose run --rm test-runner npm run test:integration
```

## Example Test Structure

```
test/integration/
├── api/
│   ├── user-creation.test.ts
│   └── user-retrieval.test.ts
├── events/
│   └── onboarding-events.test.ts
└── helpers/
    ├── db-helper.ts
    └── kafka-helper.ts
```

## Test Data Cleanup

Integration tests should:
1. Set up test data before each test
2. Clean up test data after each test
3. Use unique identifiers to avoid conflicts
4. Not affect production data
